 Book: Wonder # The Book &lsquo;Wonder&rsquo; is a book which is quite realistic. August &lsquo;Auggie&rsquo; Pullman, a ten-year-old kid, was born with a gene defect, which makes his face look &lsquo;deformed&rsquo;, as Julian describes it. Auggie was homeschooled until he was in 5th grade, and finally got to a real school.
Wonder is told from different perspectives, as for Summer&rsquo;s (Auggies friend (NOT girlfriend)), Jack&rsquo;s (Auggies friend) and Via&rsquo;s (Auggies sister) perspective. Via describes the family like this: &ldquo;Auggie is the sun. Me, mom and dad are the big planets orbiting the sun. And our relatives and friends are the little aesteroids and moons orbiting the Planets.&rdquo; Like this she describes it, and it&rsquo;s true. Other friends or Via are often closed out, as I may say, by Auggies and Vias parents. If Auggie had another operation, Via may sometimes become a little moon orbiting her mum and dad.
Juian is also a kid that&rsquo;s in Augusts new school. In the first book, &lsquo;Wonder&rsquo;, he is pictured as a mobber. But in the second book, &lsquo;Auggie and me&rsquo;, it&rsquo;s shown that even the worst mobbers have a backround. As for Julian, he got nightmares from Auggies face. Julian already got this &lsquo;Nightmare problem&rsquo; in 1rst grade, at a playdate. He and the other kid watched the movie: Harry Potter, and as Julian first saw Voldemort&rsquo;s face, &lsquo;I got a panic attack and my mom had to get me home. Since then I never was on a playdate again.&rsquo; Also, speaking of Julian&rsquo;s mom, she erased August from the class picture. Then she mailed it other moms, with the sentence:&lsquo;We want no bad memories. Only good memories, right, Julian?&rsquo;

This book is a book where you get to know a boy and a girl, both about the age of thirteen, the girl is a warrior, and the boy is a wizard.
It begins, I suppose, with the wizard boy. He is called Xar (pronouneced Zar, don&rsquo;t ask me why, spelling is WEIRD), and he is the most disobedient boy of all wizards. The girl is called Wish, and has a very frantic with fear bodyguard. This girl (despite the fact that she is a warrrior PRINCESS) loves adventures. And she will get one very soon&hellip;
But it&rsquo;s up to you, dear reader, if you will or won&rsquo;t know what soon in this story will happen to those three children!

 A Wrinkle in Time # A Wrinkle in time is a book that is very thrilling, especially for children. In the book there are three children and three witches, if you want to name women that can travel through time and space name witches&hellip;
They travel to a planet that a big &ldquo;IT&rdquo; controls. They need to rescue the father from Meg, the main character in the book, the only problem is that this is anything but easy.
I recommend this book because it has such a wonderful sweeet end. And because the three witches have a really cool secret.

 Book: Meine Freundin Roxy # Meine Freundin Roxy is a book for in tech interested children like me. Kenza Ait Si Abbou has written this cool book and Meike Topperwien has illustrated it. The book describes a little girl who finds a robot in a bush, takes it home. There together with her granny she repairs the robot and starts teaching it: She starts with simple language.
Girl: &ldquo;This is a banana. Ba-na-na&rdquo;
Roxy: &ldquo;Banana&rdquo;
Girl: &ldquo;The banana is tasty. Ba-na-na - tas-ty&rdquo;
Roxy: &ldquo;Banana - tasty&rdquo;
Girl: &ldquo;This is a sock. Sock&rdquo;
Roxy: &ldquo;Sock. Tasty&rdquo;
After a long while, she and the robot, which is named Roxy, are performing a play on stage. But, after they have performed the play, Roxy&rsquo;s owner wants to take Roxy with him. The girl explains him how much fun she had with Roxy, and then she keep her.
i like it because of the happy end, and because a GIRL has a realle cool robot named Roxy ;)
